/*
 * Simple test for DPOR.
 *
 * We here assume that a, b and c commute, and a < b < c.
 *
 * Since a,b and c commute no backtrackpoints need to be set. But the disabling relation contains that a disables
 * c and b disables c.
 */

//@ commutativity (a, b) (b, a) (a, c) (c, a) (c, b) (b, c)
//@ disabling (a, c) (b, c)

